05354 #ifndef GLEXT_64_TYPES_DEFINED
05355 /* This code block is duplicated in glxext.h, so must be protected */
05356 #define GLEXT_64_TYPES_DEFINED
05357 /* Define int32_t, int64_t, and uint64_t types for UST/MSC */
05358 /* (as used in the GL_EXT_timer_query extension). */
05359 #if defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && __STDC_VERSION__ >= 199901L
05360 #include <inttypes.h>
05361 #elif defined(__sun__) || defined(__digital__)
05362 #include <inttypes.h>
05363 #if defined(__STDC__)
05364 #if defined(__arch64__) || defined(_LP64)
05365 typedef long int int64_t;
05366 typedef unsigned long int uint64_t;
05367 #else
05368 typedef long long int int64_t;
05369 typedef unsigned long long int uint64_t;
05370 #endif /* __arch64__ */
05371 #endif /* __STDC__ */
05372 #elif defined( __VMS ) || defined(__sgi)
05373 #include <inttypes.h>
05374 #elif defined(__SCO__) || defined(__USLC__)
05375 #include <stdint.h>
05376 #elif defined(__UNIXOS2__) || defined(__SOL64__)
05377 typedef long int int32_t;
05378 typedef long long int int64_t;
05379 typedef unsigned long long int uint64_t;
05380 #elif defined(_WIN32) && defined(__GNUC__)
05381 #include <stdint.h>
05382 #elif defined(_WIN32)
05383 typedef __int32 int32_t;
05384 typedef __int64 int64_t;
05385 typedef unsigned __int64 uint64_t;
05386 #else
05387 /* Fallback if nothing above works */
05388 #include <inttypes.h>
05389 #endif
05390 #endif
05391

05394 typedef uint64_t GLuint64EXT;
05395 #endif
